status 3 for sorcery 4, status 4 for sorcery 5. Ordo Dracul status 1 is required for tiers 1, coils 1-2, status 2 is required for tier 2, coils 3-4, status 3 is coils 5-6, and status 4 for tier 3, coils 7-8, status 5 for tier 4.%0a%0a%0a[[#Guidelines]]%0a[++'''Banned at Creation but Allowed in Play'''++]%0a%0a*%0a%0a*%0a%0a%0a[[#Restricted]]%0a[++'''Restricted Items'''++]%0a%0aYou may only have 3 restricted slots at Creation.%0a%0a*Clan and Covenant status 1 is restricted, %0a%0a*Having a Bloodline at creation is 1 restricted slot if with a PC or NPC sire. It is 2 restricted slots without.%0a%0a*1 Restricted slot per 50 years in the Requiem. (Current max is at 70 years. This may increase at a later date)%0a%0a*Devotions can be bought at character creation for one restricted slot each.%0a%0a[[#Banned]]%0a[++'''Banned Items'''++]%0a%0a%0a%0a[--%25color=#A00000%25[[#vtop| Back to top]]--]%0a%0a%0a[[#Bloodlines]]%0a[++'''Bloodlines'''++]%0a%0aBloodlines come in three tiers, each handled slightly differently. This is the policy as it stands, the one we'll be using to approve characters.%0a%0a1) Preferred Bloodlines. This list will be reviewed regularly. It includes a series of lines we feel are conducive to the setting, and we have material planned for. If you want to start with one of these lines, you may do so at character creation for one restricted slot and a dot of Willpower, if you start play with Blood Potency 2. Note that we will review the list, and bloodlines that seem to have strong in-character relationships will be considered for addition.%0a%0a%0a%0a%0a[[#Ghouls]]%0a[++'''Ghouls'''++]%0a%0aGhoul families are now allowed.%0a%0a[--%25color=#A00000%25[[#vtop| Back to top]]--]%0a%0a(:include CityBook.VampireNavigationBar:)
