mples must be built IC, not allowed at creation.%0a%3c %0a%3c *Altar is restricted, but may be built IC.%0a%3c %0a%3c *Shadow cults must be created or joined in-game, cannot start with Initiation.%0a%3c %0a%3c *Carthian interest groups must be created IC. %0a%3c %0a%3c *Carthian Pull must be gained IC.%0a%3c %0a%3c *Tenancy may be taken at creation only with the express permission of the area governor. This may slow down your approval process, as the STs need to confer with another player. However, we encourage receiving tenancy IC for character development.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#Restricted]]%0a%3c [++'''Restricted Items'''++]%0a%3c %0a%3c You may only have 3 restricted slots at Creation.%0a%3c %0a%3c *Clan and Covenant status 1 is restricted, %0a%3c %0a%3c *Having a Bloodline at creation is 1 restricted slot if with a PC or NPC sire. It is 2 restricted slots without.%0a%3c %0a%3c *1 Restricted slot per 50 years in the Requiem. (Current max is at 70 years. This may increase at a later date)%0a%3c %0a%3c *Devotions can be bought at character creation for one restricted slot each.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#Banned]]%0a%3c [++'''Banned Items'''++]%0a%3c %0a%3c *Carthian Lawyer is not allowed. %0a%3c %0a%3c *Invictus dynastic merits are not available.%0a%3c %0a%3c *The Good/Bad Breeding merits from the Ventrue clanbook are not available for use at this time.%0a%3c %0a%3c *Banned Bloodlines are the following: Bohagande, Norvegi%0a%3c %0a%3c [--%25color=#A00000%25[[#vtop| Back to top]]--]%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#Bloodlines]]%0a%3c [++'''Bloodlines'''++]%0a%3c %0a%3c Bloodlines come in three tiers, each handled slightly differently. This is the policy as it stands, the one we'll be using to approve characters.%0a%3c %0a%3c 1) Preferred Bloodlines. This list will be reviewed regularly. It includes a series of lines we feel are conducive to the setting, and we have material planned for. If you want to start with one of these lines, you may do so at character creation for one restricted slot and a dot of Willpower, if you start play with Blood Potency 2. Note that we will review the list, and bloodlines that seem to have strong in-character relationships will be considered for addition.%0a%3c %0a%3c Bruja, Kallisti, Malkovian, Shepherds, Toreador, California Xiao, Spina%0a%3c %0a%3c 2) Other bloodlines. We'll review the vast majority on a case-for-case basis. If you choose to develop one of these, you may at creation with ST approval. %0a%3c %0a%3c 3) Banned bloodlines. We'll try to keep this list as limited as possible. These are lines we absolutely will not approve, because we feel they're counter to the game we're trying to run. They are listed under banned items.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#Tijuana]]%0a%3c [++'''Tijuana origins for PC's'''++]%0a%3c %0a%3c Tijuana is currently at war with San Diego. You may have a character sired by an NPC in Tijuana and you have escaped the brutal regime there. Keep in mind, Tijuana vampires are largely antagonists, your sire may make an appearance (and could make a good story). There are, however, no Carthians or Ordo Dracul in Tijuana.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#Ghouls]]%0a%3c [++'''Ghouls'''++]%0a%3c %0a%3c Ghoul families are now allowed.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#IncentiveXP]]%0a%3c [++'''Incentive XP'''++]%0a%3c %0a%3c Characters can haxe a maximum of 5 Venue iXP and 5 General iXP, for a total of 10 iXP.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[http://www.wantonwicked.net/forum/viewtopic.php?f=250&t=32374|General iXP]]%0a%3c %0a%3c Venue iXP:%0a%3c %0a%3c *+1iXP Established NPC sire%0a%3c *+3iXP PC sire%0a%3c *+1iXP Sire is *not* an Elder.%0a%3c %0a%3c *+1iXP Under 40 years into requiem%0a%3c *+2iXP Under 20 years into requiem%0a%3c ->Not cumulative.%0a%3c %0a%3c *+1iXP No bloodline%0a%3c %0a%3c *+2iXP the Mekhet or Nosferatu clans.%0a%3c %0a%3c *+1iXP the Ventrue Clan%0a%3c %0a%3c *+2iXP the Ordo Dracul Covenant%0a%3c %0a%3c Ghouls iXP:%0a%3c %0a%3c *+2iXP Ghoul is not from a Ghoul Family%0a%3c %0a%3c *+1iXP Is 40 years or less into Ghouling.%0a%3c *+2iXP Is 20 